
// This Hyperlambda code constructs a connection string by concatenating a predefined format with values from the [.arguments] node. The [set-value] slot assigns this concatenated string to the [.connection] node. The [strings.concat] slot combines the connection string and database name, separated by a pipe character and enclosed in square brackets. The [get-value] slots retrieve these values from the [.arguments] node.
set-value:x:@.connection
   strings.concat
      .:[
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/connection-string
      .:|
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/database
      .:]
